\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The purpose of this policy is to establish the governance and operational framework for the Department's Knowledge Base as the single authoritative repository of operational procedures,
 workarounds,
 Known Error entries,
 Standard change pre-authorization procedures,
 deployment procedures,
 tool configurations,
 runbooks,
 and reference documentation.
 This policy governs the creation,
 maintenance,
 review,
 and retirement of all knowledge artifacts and serves as the authorization backbone for Standard change classification under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy applies to all Information Operations Department personnel and governs all knowledge artifacts created,
 maintained,
 or retired by the Department.
 In-scope artifact types include operational procedures,
 workaround and resolution documentation,
 Known Error entries,
 Standard change pre-authorization procedures,
 Standard deployment procedures,
 system and tool configurations,
 monitoring runbooks,
 escalation paths,
 service delivery workflows,
 and reference documentation.
\end_layout

