\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.6 Documentation-Before-Closure Obligation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Any task executed without a corresponding KB entry shall result in creation or revision of a KB article prior to work order closure.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.7 Review and Retirement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
All KB entries shall be reviewed no less than annually or following any Significant or Emergency change affecting a documented procedure or reference artifact.
 Only the IT Director shall authorize formal retirement of any KB article.
 Retired articles shall be marked inactive and retained for a minimum of six (6) calendar years after supersession or official abandonment,
 in accordance with Nevada Local Government Records Retention Schedule LRDA 20070057.
 All KB content is operationally confidential;
 external distribution requires written IT Director authorization.
\end_layout

